Impression and Plan
Course: Progressing as expected.
Patient Instructions: Counseled: Patient, Regarding diagnosis, Verbalized understanding.
Dx and Plan
This is a 53 year-old female, s/p 11/29 Ray reaection of ring and small finger Rti hand. POG: pt was scheduled for po apt on 12/16, coming in today d/t concern of dehiscence and possible infection. pt staying at Life Care of Andover rehab facility currently. pt doing dialysis. Based on today's assessment, patient is healing and progressing as expected at this time following the procedure. I recommend proceeding with wet to dry dressing changes once a day at the incision site for continued progression and healing. I also stressed to the patient the importance of regular consumption of protein in the diet as the body continues to further repair and heal. Patient expressed an understanding and is in agreement with the plan moving forward. All questions were answered today, and the patient was counseled to call the clinic with any other questions.
